cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the training process of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and their behavior from a Fourier analysis perspective. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the regularity of commonly used activation functions, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The benchmark datasets used in the paper are image datasets, which suggests the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the convergence behavior of iterative numerical schemes, which falls under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization of DNNs on real datasets and parity function or randomized dataset, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
